<p>I am using WSO2 ESB 4.8.1. Similar to the issue as reported in: <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/26740855/wso2-esb-jms-response-from-endpoint-with-xml-payload-shows-up-as-text">WSO2 ESB - JMS response from endpoint with XML payload shows up as Text</a>, WSO2 ESB wraps and encodes the entire XML payload as returned from JMS response inside a <code>&lt;</code>text<code>&gt;</code> tag and then insert this tag into another XML. Below is my WSO2 ESB proxy configuration:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;proxy xmlns="http://ws.apache.org/ns/synapse"    name="JSONProxy"    transports="https,http"    statistics="disable"    trace="disable"    startOnLoad="true"&gt;    &lt;target&gt;   &lt;inSequence&gt;          &lt;log&gt;         &lt;property xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"                   name="JSON-Request"                   expression="json-eval($.)"/&gt;      &lt;/log&gt;          &lt;property name="transport.jms.ContentTypeProperty"                value="Content-Type"                scope="axis2"/&gt;      &lt;xslt key="in_transform"/&gt;      &lt;header name="Action" scope="default" value="urn:getQuote"/&gt;          &lt;enrich&gt;         &lt;source xmlns:m0="http://services.samples"                 xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"                 clone="true"                 xpath="//m0:getQuote"/&gt;         &lt;target type="body"/&gt;      &lt;/enrich&gt;          &lt;property name="messageType" value="text/xml" scope="axis2"/&gt;   &lt;/inSequence&gt;   &lt;outSequence&gt;      &lt;log level="full"/&gt;      &lt;property name="messageType"                value="application/json"                scope="axis2"                type="STRING"/&gt;      &lt;send/&gt;   &lt;/outSequence&gt;       &lt;endpoint&gt;      &lt;address uri="jms:/SMSStore?transport.jms.ConnectionFactoryJNDIName=QueueConnectionFactory&amp;amp;java.naming.factory.initial=org.apache.activemq.jndi.ActiveMQInitialContextFactory&amp;amp;java.naming.provider.url=tcp://localhost:61616&amp;amp;transport.jms.DestinationType=queue"               format="soap11"/&gt;   &lt;/endpoint&gt;    &lt;/target&gt;    &lt;description/&gt; &lt;/proxy&gt; </code></pre>  <p>If I link the above proxy to an HTTP response (also in XML) instead, the result would then work as expected, without the need to change the above proxy configuration.</p>  <p>Would greatly appreciate any help/suggestion in resolving this. Many thanks in advance!</p>